<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00 Congress, Communist International,
                            VII/63: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-21T19:00:00+03:00">August 21,
                                    1935—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 21—3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>370. Personal for the President. I have just written an indecently long
                            telegram on the Communist Congress. I wish I could have talked with you,
                            the Secretary, <persName corresp="#p_MRW1">Moore</persName> and
                                <persName corresp="#p_KRF1">Kelley</persName> instead. The main
                            point is to handle the matter from the domestic, not the foreign,
                            political viewpoint. If by any chance you decide to follow the line I
                            have recommended, do have <persName corresp="#p_KRF1">Kelley</persName>
                            in on all drafting. The technical complexities of Soviet organization
                            are so great that his encyclopedic knowledge will be indispensable.
                            Whatever you do, the Bolsheviks will make it hot for us here. But, as
                            Judge <persName corresp="#p_MRW1">Moore</persName> says, we are already
                            accustomed to Hades and acclimated. Love to your whole White House
                            family and yourself.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>